 is a good choice for going over an oil-based primer but a 100 percent acrylic exterior paint can also be suitable.";i:6;s:60:"Use a large brush to cut down on your overall painting time.";i:7;s:113:"You can use a roller but they are much harder to clean if you use oil-based paint so a brush is usually a better.";i:8;s:93:"Latex paint is what you want to use when painting the interior of your garage in 99 of cases.";i:9;s:68:"It is sometimes referred to as acrylic paint and they work the same.";i:10;s:115:"They have much lower levels of chemical vapors can be thinned out with water dry faster and cleanup is much easier.";i:11;s:52:"How To Paint A Garage Door - Ace Hardware - YouTube.";i:12;s:74:"Your garage is one of the first things you see when you look at your home.";i:13;s:36:"Treat it with a fresh coat of paint.";i:14;s:44:"Well show you how to paint your garage door.";i:15;s:166:"Since the best paint for garage walls is essentially standard interior paint that is well suited for garage environments it is available in the five typical finishes.";i:16;s:26:"Matte eggshell satin semi.";i:17;s:138:"As we said before you can use interior or exterior paint on your garage walls depending on where you live and the kind of garage you have.";i:18;s:85:"If you have an attached garage in a moderate climate your best bet is interior paint.";i:19;s:37:"You can also use an existing stencil.";i:20;s:42:"Tape your stencil in place on the doormat.";i:21;s:92:"It wont stick completely because of the coir material but it will help a bit while painting.";i:22;s:20:"I used packing tape.";i:23;s:83:"Paint the design in using a poking method to ensure the paint doesnt look splotchy.";i:24;s:60:"Poking instead of brushing is necessary because of the coir.";i:25;s:112:"Latex paint dries faster is water based has minimal odor and can be thinned with water instead of paint thinner.";i:26;s:81:"Oil takes longer to dry has a strong odor and you must use paint thinner to thin.";i:27;s:60:"G